race.comment: They've been spacing the runs of TOWER OF TUSCANY (10) this spring and it seems to be working. Although he hasn't cracked it for that elusive second win, he's racing very well and looks to have found a winnable assignment here. Milnes sticks and she should be able to find a spot in the first half of the field with cover. He can win. FLAMING NAVY (5) looks one of the leaders and he's definitely going to take some beating. He's won two from six and looks progressive. If he can get across from the wide gate without doing too much work, he can hold on. Happy to forgive the last start run of COLLATED (4), who was well supported and looked to have every chance. His prior form is good and he looks capable of rising through the grades. WORSFOLD (2) hasn't done much wrong since joining the new stable and looks a top-three chance again, while ENLIST (9) is an old warrior that can run a cheeky race for exotics and quaddies.
